@Jakkar_Ruus your analogy comparing $NVDA and $SIVEF is severely flawed. Using PE or revenue etc as a foundation for why stocks trade at a certain price could be justified in the 1970s and 1980s, but todays Wall Street doesn't work that way. Its sad actually that it doesn't. We have stocks that go up 1000% in a year and the companies are garbage, some with no revenue and drowning in debt.

We arent marrying a company. We trade for making money. Small caps can return significantly more upside than a behemoth like NVDA. Just the fact. More risk yes but more upside.

$SIVEF can triple or quadruple in price here this year regardless of what their PE is etc. I dont believe nvda would even double in price over the next year.

